A vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration showing a commercial airplane flying high above a stylized European landscape at night, with glowing cellular tower signals rising up from tiny villages below like luminous spires. The plane leaves a gentle contrail while colorful radio waves in amber, teal, and coral arc upward from different country territories, each wave pattern slightly different to suggest crossing borders. The composition uses bold, flat colors with subtle grain texture, muted midnight blues for the sky contrasted with warm golden lights from the ground. The perspective is from beside the aircraft looking down at the patchwork of nations below, each emitting their own distinct signal glow into the stratosphere.
